<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-56-0689 </DOCNO><TEXT>In this paper we describe how path reconstruction of scattered particlescan be used to improve the resolution of magnetic spectrometers. Correctionmatrix elements can be optimized off-line. The method described resultedin a resolution of 7x10/sup -5/ over the full solid angle for the QDDspectrometer at the NIKHEF-K electron scattering facility.</TEXT></DOC>